<section xml:id="C6.S7">
<title>Integral Representations</title>        
  
<subsection xml:id="C6.S7.SS1">
<title>Exponential Integrals</title>        
 
<para xml:id="C6.S7.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C6.S7.SS1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="6.7.1" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E1">\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-at}}{t+b}\mathrm{d}t=\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{e^{iat} }{t+ib}\mathrm{d}t=e^{ab}E_{1}\left(ab\right), if a&gt;0, b&gt;0,</Math> <Math equation-number="6.7.2" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E2">e^{x}\int_{0}^{\alpha}\frac{e^{-xt}}{1-t}\mathrm{d}t=\mathrm{Ei}\left(x\right) -\mathrm{Ei}\left((1-\alpha)x\right), if 0\leq\alpha&lt;1, x&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C6.S7.SS1.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="6.7.3" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E3">\int_{x}^{\infty}\frac{e^{it}}{a^{2}+t^{2}}\mathrm{d}t=\frac{i}{2a}\left(e^{a} E_{1}\left(a-ix\right)-e^{-a}E_{1}\left(-a-ix\right)\right), if a&gt;0, x&gt;0,</Math> <Math equation-number="6.7.4" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E4">\int_{x}^{\infty}\frac{te^{it}}{a^{2}+t^{2}}\mathrm{d}t=\tfrac{1}{2}\left(e^{a }E_{1}\left(a-ix\right)+e^{-a}E_{1}\left(-a-ix\right)\right), if a&gt;0, x&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C6.S7.SS1.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="6.7.5" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E5">\int_{x}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-t}}{a^{2}+t^{2}}\mathrm{d}t=-\frac{1}{2ai}\left(e^{ ia}E_{1}\left(x+ia\right)-e^{-ia}E_{1}\left(x-ia\right)\right), if a&gt;0, x\in\mathbb{R},</Math> <Math equation-number="6.7.6" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E6">\int_{x}^{\infty}\frac{te^{-t}}{a^{2}+t^{2}}\mathrm{d}t=\tfrac{1}{2}\left(e^{ ia}E_{1}\left(x+ia\right)+e^{-ia}E_{1}\left(x-ia\right)\right), if a&gt;0, x\in\mathbb{R}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C6.S7.SS1.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="6.7.7" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E7">\int_{0}^{1}\frac{e^{-at}\sin\left(bt\right)}{t}\mathrm{d}t=\Im\mathrm{Ein} \left(a+ib\right), if a,b\in\mathbb{R},</Math> <Math equation-number="6.7.8" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E8">\int_{0}^{1}\frac{e^{-at}(1-\cos\left(bt\right))}{t}\mathrm{d}t=\Re\mathrm{Ein }\left(a+ib\right)-\mathrm{Ein}\left(a\right), if a,b\in\mathbb{R}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C6.S7.SS1.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C6.S7.SS1.p2.s1">
Many integrals with exponentials and rational functions, for example, integrals of the type <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C6.S7.SS1.p2.m1">\int e^{z}R(z)\mathrm{d}z</Math> , where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C6.S7.SS1.p2.m2">R(z)</Math> is an arbitrary rationalfunction, can be represented in finite form in terms of the function <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C6.S7.SS1.p2.m3">E_{1}\left(z\right)</Math> and elementary functions; see Lebedev (1965, p. 42).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C6.S7.SS2">
<title>Sine and Cosine Integrals</title>        
   
<para xml:id="C6.S7.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C6.S7.SS2.p1.s1">
When <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C6.S7.SS2.p1.m1">z\in\mathbb{C}</Math> <Math equation-number="6.7.9" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E9">\mathrm{si}\left(z\right)=-\int_{0}^{\pi/2}e^{-z\cos t}\cos\left(z\sin t\right )\mathrm{d}t,</Math> <Math equation-number="6.7.10" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E10">\mathrm{Ein}\left(z\right)-\mathrm{Cin}\left(z\right)=\int_{0}^{\pi/2}e^{-z \cos t}\sin\left(z\sin t\right)\mathrm{d}t,</Math> <Math equation-number="6.7.11" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E11">\int_{0}^{1}\frac{(1-e^{-at})\cos\left(bt\right)}{t}\mathrm{d}t=\Re\mathrm{Ein }\left(a+ib\right)-\mathrm{Cin}\left(b\right), if a,b\in\mathbb{R}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C6.S7.SS3">
<title>Auxiliary Functions</title>        
  
<para xml:id="C6.S7.SS3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C6.S7.SS3.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="6.7.12" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E12">\mathrm{g}\left(z\right)+i\mathrm{f}\left(z\right)=e^{-iz}\int_{z}^{\infty} \frac{e^{it}}{t}\mathrm{d}t, if |\operatorname{ph}z|\leq\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C6.S7.SS3.p1.s2">
The path of integration does not cross the negative real axis or pass through the origin.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C6.S7.SS3.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="6.7.13" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E13">\mathrm{f}\left(z\right)=\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{\sin t}{t+z}\mathrm{d}t=\int_{ 0}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-zt}}{t^{2}+1}\mathrm{d}t,</Math> , <Math equation-number="6.7.14" mode="display" xml:id="C6.S7.E14">\mathrm{g}\left(z\right)=\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{\cos t}{t+z}\mathrm{d}t=\int_{ 0}^{\infty}\frac{te^{-zt}}{t^{2}+1}\mathrm{d}t</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C6.S7.SS3.p1.s4">
